There was a time when earning a college degree, any college degree, was a nearly ironclad guarantee of a lucrative, fulfilling career.
When you take accruing loan interest, loan repayments, and declining income growth into account, many college degrees are no longer wise investments.
Not All Degrees Are Created EqualOverall, having a college degree is still generally better than not having one.
The comparisons get a little fuzzier when you compare bachelor’s degrees to graduate and professional degrees.
Big Picture TakeawaysLooking at the overall findings of the study makes one thing clear: about half of our assumptions about the value of college degrees simply aren’t supported by the facts.